cs.DC, cs.PF, cs.AR, cs.PL, cs.LG 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses scheduling parallel applications on a heterogeneous hybrid architecture. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is also likely as the paper focuses on optimizing scheduling to improve performance. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses scheduling between CPUs and GPUs. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses porting PLASMA library kernels onto the XKaapi runtime system. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses dense linear algebra kernels, which are commonly used in machine learning applications.
